articles.title: Asia-Pacific markets track Wall Street gains; South Korea unexpectedly keeps rates unchanged - CNBC
articles.description: Korea's central bank surprised market watchers by keeping base rates unchanged at 3%.
articles.content:
Asia-Pacific markets mostly climbed Thursday, after U.S. markets soared on the back of an unexpected decline in core inflation numbers in December and strong bank earnings.
